# {{ cookiecutter.project_name }} — frontend (React skeleton)

> Minimal React 19 + Vite 7 + TypeScript 6 skeleton. No router, no auth, no UI library — bring your own.
>
> What's wired for you: the Vite dev proxy to Django, the OWASP-conscious defaults, the Compose service, and the `pnpm-workspace.yaml` tying frontend to backend.

## Run it

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev                          # vite on http://localhost:{{ cookiecutter.frontend_dev_port }}
# OR
docker compose -f compose.local.yml up
```

