## OWASP Top 10 baseline (already on)

Even in skeleton form, these defenses are NOT negotiable:

- **A01 Broken Access Control** — every authoritative check lives on the Django side. Add client-side guards as UX only.
- **A02 Crypto Failures** — session cookies (HttpOnly) are the only credential. NEVER store a JWT in `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` — that's an XSS-to-takeover gun.
- **A03 Injection / XSS** — React auto-escapes; `react/no-danger` ESLint rule bans the raw-HTML API.
- **A05 Misconfig** — Vite proxies `/api` + `/_allauth` to Django so cookies stay first-party; never enable wildcard CORS.
- **A06 Vulnerable Components** — pin majors in `package.json`; run `pnpm audit --prod` in CI; let Renovate update.
- **A08 Integrity** — `pnpm-lock.yaml` committed; no `latest` tags.
- **A09 Logging** — server-side; the SPA never logs request bodies (no credentials in console).

## Adding what you need

| Want | Drop in |
| --- | --- |
| Routing | `pnpm add react-router` |
| Auth (recommended pattern) | Copy `frontend/src/auth/` from the [django-bakery Full template](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery/tree/main/crates/templates/files/%7B%7Bcookiecutter.project_slug%7D%7D) — it's a typed allauth-headless client; never invent your own |
| UI library | `pnpm add @radix-ui/themes` · `pnpm add @mui/material` · or copy shadcn components |
| State | `pnpm add zustand` (lightweight) · `pnpm add @tanstack/react-query` (server state) |
| Tests | `pnpm add -D vitest jsdom @testing-library/react @playwright/test` |

## Calling the backend

The Vite proxy makes `/api/*` and `/_allauth/*` first-party requests. From any component:

```tsx
const me = await fetch("/api/me", {
  credentials: "include",   // session cookie
}).then((r) => r.json());
```

If your project uses **Django Ninja** (`api_layer = ninja`), the backend uses `django_auth` — session-based. See [django-ninja auth docs](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/).
If it uses **DRF** (`api_layer = drf`), the backend uses `SessionAuthentication` — see [DRF auth docs](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/).

In both cases the session cookie from `/_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login` is the only thing you need.
